# Content agent orchestration

Hard limits on **Cursor tools**, **shell**, and **MCP** live in **`strict-tool-boundaries.mdc`** ‚Äî read both when editing or dispatching.

- **User-requested agent = real dispatch, not persona:** When the user explicitly asks to **use / invoke / run / call / Task** a named agent, the assistant **must** **`Task`** that agent (see **`mode-auto-selection.mdc`** ‚Äî explicit invocation gate). **Never** substitute in-chat imitation of **`cco`**, **`content-lead`**, or specialist tone for a missing **`Task`**.

- **Task-first tool contract (parent chat ‚Äî non-negotiable):** When **`mode-auto-selection`** says the user **invoked** an agent (including **delegate / assign / hand off / orchestrate with** patterns), the **parent** session **must** emit **`Task`** with matching **`subagent_type`** **before** any **mutating** tool on the corpus / `.cursor` / vault paths for that request. **Violations** (drafting plans, running pipeline stages, or editing atoms **before** dispatch when the user named **`cco`** / **`content-lead`** / **`video-editor`** / **`chief-visual-officer`** / project **`sme-*`** / **`reviewer-*`**) are **routing failures** ‚Äî **stop**, **admit the miss**, **`Task`** the named agent with the original brief. **Never** substitute main-chat ‚ÄúI'll do the CCO plan inline‚Äù for a missing child run.

- **Subagent orchestration ‚Äî zero-gap (hard):** A **hop** = one **`Task`** completion (or explicit protocol **`malformed`/`degraded`** stub) before the parent claims that agent‚Äôs work. **No gap** means: (1) **every** slice the user sees as ‚Äúfrom **`cco`** / **`content-lead`** / **`sme-*`** / **CVO** / **`vp-research`**‚Äù was produced by that agent‚Äôs **`Task`** (orchestrator may **merge** only per **`subagent-response-protocol`** ‚Äî **no** new copy, claims, or paths); (2) **no** parent turn interleaves corpus **writes** with **pending** child work on the same atoms; (3) **`cco`** and **`content-lead`** **never** impersonate **`editorial-cro`**, internal personas, or project SMEs ‚Äî dispatch or block; (4) parallel **`Task`** = **disjoint `touches[]`** only; overlap ‚Üí **stop**, redelegate. **Impersonation** of a child = **always** a violation.

## Entrypoints

- **Planning episode (content org):** Any **multi-step editorial plan** from **any** agent that owns the episode ‚Äî typically **`cco`**. **Plan artifact** = **persisted** `<project>/.cursor/docs/plans/*.md` **or** **prompt-only** (final plan in chat). **Prefer** disk; **`editorial-cro-loop`** still mandatory before corpus execution when user signals implement. **`cco`** may run the loop as **surrogate** if another agent authored the plan.
- **`cco`** ‚Äî plan mode; writes `<project>/.cursor/docs/plans/*.md` when possible (content work repo ‚Äî not dotfiles pack paths); may parallel-invoke content specialists; after v0, **post‚Äìv0 edit round** (ask once whether to add/remove/change anything; optional revisions); runs **`editorial-cro-loop`** **once** when user signals **implement / execute / proceed with implementation** ‚Äî **before** **`content-lead`** or corpus execution (same if **`cco`** is surrogate for a prompt-only plan); **`editorial-cro`** / loop MUST apply the **full structured editorial rubric** (**conditional depth** per plan complexity per agent/skill), not impressionistic expansion alone; may **`Task`** **`chief-visual-officer`** when visual deliverables are in scope; may **`Task`** **`video-editor`** for programmatic-video planning help; may **`Task`** **`remotion-builder`** **only** when the user explicitly asks **`cco`** to dispatch it in planning (or plan records one-off user sign-off) ‚Äî **not** from routing-table auto-classification alone; may **`Task`** **`chief-profile-metrics`** / **`chief-growth-strategy`** when the plan names browser profile capture or growth intelligence phases.
- **`content-lead`** ‚Äî execution; discovers `{root}/.cursor/agents/` via **`content-team-discovery`**, **and** registers org singleton **`chief-visual-officer`** when **`chief-visual-handoff`** applies; when **`approved_plan_path`** names a **`video-editor`** / programmatic-video phase, satisfies **`video-editor-handoff`** then **`Task` `remotion-builder`**; runs **`generate-content-pipeline`** stages, **`content-git-workflow`** when policy says push; may **`Task`** **`chief-profile-metrics`** / **`chief-growth-strategy`** when the approved plan‚Äôs phase lists them.

## Org singleton: `chief-visual-officer` (CVO)

- **Location:** **`~/.cursor/agents/chief-visual-officer.md`** when this pack is stowed ‚Äî **do not** duplicate the role in `<project>/.cursor/agents/`.
- **Callers:** **`cco`**, **`content-lead`**, org **`vp-*`**, **`cpo`**, **`staff-editor`**, **`editorial-ops-lead`**, and **project** SMEs ‚Äî all may **`Task`** CVO with a payload meeting [**`chief-visual-handoff`**](../skills/chief-visual-handoff/SKILL.md). This is **not** a lateral project‚Üí`vp-*` violation; CVO is the designated visual execution agent.
- **Model:** **`composer-2`**, pinned in CVO frontmatter.

## No Atlassian / no org QA

- **`atlassian-pm`** is **not** part of this pack.  
- No org-tier **`qa-*`**; human reviews after automation; optional plan-only critic is **`editorial-cro`**.

## Subagent protocol

Child `Task` returns: **`subagent-response-protocol.mdc`** + YAML envelope per inject hook. Parent parse contract same as org standard.

## Execution approval

- **Interactive:** explicit checkpoint wording per phase (silence ‚âÝ approval).  
- **Automation (`execution_mode: automation`):** no chat gates; **`content-git-workflow`** + n8n payloads per **`orchestration.mdc`**.

## Escalation

- Project agents ‚Üí **`cco`** for replanning (no lateral org `Task` chains from project tier **to `vp-*` / `cpo` / `staff-editor`** for new strategy).
- **Exception:** project agents **may** **`Task`** org **`chief-visual-officer`** for visual execution when **`chief-visual-handoff`** preconditions are met (same as **`content-lead`**).
- **`editorial-cro`** findings with `bounce_target` ‚Üí only **planning-episode owner** (typically **`cco`**) issues specialist `Task`s.

