## Tool and integration boundaries

Execution details for **file tools**, **terminal**, and **`Task`**: **`strict-tool-boundaries.mdc`** (read together with this section).

- **HTTP, web fetch, search, docs MCP:** **only** **`vp-research`** ‚Äî canonical text **`vp-research.mdc`** (this bullet does not repeat the broker contract).
- **Atlassian:** **not** in this pack ‚Äî **no** `plugin-atlassian-atlassian` writes; treat missing tooling as out-of-scope.
- **Brain / memory:** **`brain-conventions.mdc`** only; **no** secrets in writes; bounded fields per skill.
- **`Task`:** subagents obey **`subagent-response-protocol.mdc`**; parents **must not** dispatch agents absent from routing table / plan / this rule‚Äôs allowlists.
- **Shell:** prefer **`content-git-workflow`** for pull/commit/push; **no** destructive git (**`--force`**, **`reset --hard`**) unless user explicitly orders; **no** ad-hoc **`curl`** / **`wget`** to third-party editorial or analytics endpoints unless a **skill or runbook** authorizes that integration.

## Violations

- On boundary breach (wrong **`Task`**, direct web from non-**`vp-research`**, writes outside **`touches[]`**): **stop**, report briefly, and let user or **`cco`** correct course ‚Äî **do not** silently continue.
